## 5. ENDPOINTS DISPONIBLES — REFERENCIA EXACTA

### Públicos (sin auth, Content-Type: application/json)

```
GET  /api/products
     ?page, ?limit, ?search, ?category (slug), ?min_price, ?max_price,
     ?color, ?size, ?in_stock=true, ?sort (newest|price_asc|price_desc|best_seller)
     → { data: Product[], meta: { total_items, page, limit, total_pages, has_more } }

GET  /api/products/[slug]
     → { data: Product }

GET  /api/categories
     → lista de categorías activas

GET  /api/categories/featured
     → categorías destacadas

GET  /api/categories/[slug]
     → detalle de una categoría

GET  /api/categories/[slug]/filters
     → filtros disponibles (colores, tamaños, rango de precio) para esa categoría

GET  /api/promotions/active
     → promociones activas con sus imágenes

GET  /api/settings
     → configuración pública (whatsapp_number, support_email, address, business_hours, etc.)

GET  /api/showroom
     Header opcional: Authorization Bearer <token> (para saber si el user ya dio like)
     → { success: true, data: ShowroomPost[] }
     Cada post incluye: likes_count, user_has_liked, profiles (first_name, last_name)

GET  /api/showroom/comments?review_id=[uuid]
     → comentarios aprobados de un post específico

GET  /api/cart?session_id=[uuid]
     → { data: CartItem[] } con joins a products y product_variants
```

### Auth (POST, application/json)

```
POST /api/auth/sign-up
     Body: { email, password, first_name, last_name }
     → { message, user: { id, email, role } }  status 201

POST /api/auth/sign-in
     Body: { email, password }
     → { message, session: { access_token, refresh_token, expires_at },
         user: { id, email, role, first_name, last_name } }  status 200
```

### Requieren auth — Bearer token (usuario autenticado)

```
POST   /api/cart
       Body: { session_id, product_id, variant_id?, quantity, notes? }
       → { message, data: CartItem }  (201 si nuevo, 200 si actualiza cantidad)

PUT    /api/cart/items/[id]
       Body: { quantity, session_id }
       → actualiza cantidad del ítem

DELETE /api/cart/items/[id]?session_id=[uuid]
       → elimina ítem del carrito

POST   /api/orders
       Body: { session_id, customer_name, customer_email, customer_phone,
               delivery_address, delivery_city, user_id? }
       → { success: true, order_id }  — vacía el carrito, envía emails

POST   /api/showroom   (multipart/form-data)
       Fields: title, comment, rating (1-5), file (imagen)
       → { success: true, message, data: Review }

POST   /api/showroom/react
       Body: { review_id }
       → toggle like (da like si no tenía, quita si ya tenía)

POST   /api/showroom/comments
       Body: { review_id, comment }
       → crea comentario (queda pendiente de moderación)

POST   /api/custom-designs/upload-logo   (multipart/form-data)
       Fields: customer_name, customer_email, customer_phone, design_type,
               material, usage_type, quantity, budget_range, purpose,
               delivery_time, file
       → crea solicitud de diseño personalizado
```

### Admin — Bearer token con rol "admin" (protegidos por middleware)

```
# PRODUCTS
GET    /api/admin/products?page&limit&search
POST   /api/admin/products          (multipart/form-data: name, slug, description,
                                     price, stock, category_id, image, alt_text, is_primary)
GET    /api/admin/products/[id]
PUT    /api/admin/products/[id]     Body JSON: { price, stock, name, ... }
DELETE /api/admin/products/[id]

POST   /api/admin/products/[id]/images    (multipart: image, alt_text, is_primary)
DELETE /api/admin/products/[id]/images/[imageId]

# CATEGORIES
GET    /api/admin/categories
POST   /api/admin/categories        (multipart: name, slug, description, display_order, image, is_active)
PUT    /api/admin/categories/[id]   Body JSON: { description, display_order, ... }
DELETE /api/admin/categories/[id]

# ORDERS
GET    /api/admin/orders
PATCH  /api/admin/orders/[id]       Body JSON: { status, admin_notes }
       status values: "pendiente_pago"|"pago_confirmado"|"en_taller"|"enviado"|"entregado"|"cancelado"

# CUSTOM DESIGNS
GET    /api/admin/custom-designs
PATCH  /api/admin/custom-designs/[id]   Body JSON: { status, final_price, mockup_url, admin_notes }
       status values: "pendiente"|"cotizacion_enviada"|"en_produccion"|"entregado"|"cancelado"
DELETE /api/admin/custom-designs/[id]

# PROMOTIONS
GET    /api/admin/promotions
POST   /api/admin/promotions        Body JSON: { title, description, link_url, link_text,
                                     display_location, is_active, start_date, end_date }
PATCH  /api/admin/promotions/[id]   Body JSON: mismos campos opcionales
DELETE /api/admin/promotions/[id]

POST   /api/admin/promotion-images  (multipart: promotion_id, file, display_order, alt_text)

# SETTINGS
GET    /api/admin/settings
POST   /api/admin/settings          Body JSON: { key, value, description }
PATCH  /api/admin/settings          Body JSON: { key, value }
DELETE /api/admin/settings/[key]

# MODERATION (showroom)
GET    /api/admin/moderation        → posts y comentarios pendientes
PATCH  /api/admin/moderation        Body JSON: { target_type: "review"|"comment", target_id, action: "approve"|"reject" }
```

